 {"id":"frankenjax-bw7","title":"Implement complex rem and atan2 in apply_complex_binary (fj-lax arithmetic.rs)","description":"WHAT: Add complex remainder and atan2 to apply_complex_binary() in crates/fj-lax/src/arithmetic.rs:145-164.\nWHERE: Same match arm as complex pow — the catch-all at line 160.\nHOW: Complex rem: z1 % z2 = z1 - z2 * floor(z1/z2) using complex division and floor on real/imag parts separately. Complex atan2: generally not well-defined for complex numbers — JAX raises an error. We should match JAX behavior: return a principled UnsupportedOperation error (not \"not yet implemented\").\nWHY: Completing the binary op coverage. For atan2, the right answer is an explicit \"not supported for complex\" error rather than \"not yet implemented\" (which implies deferred work).\nDEPENDS ON: Complex pow implementation (shares the same code path).\nTESTING: Test complex rem for simple cases. Test that complex atan2 returns UnsupportedOperation.\nACCEPTANCE: No \"not yet implemented\" string remains in apply_complex_binary.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T23:27:23.062811293Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T00:21:03.366878562Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T00:21:03.366617277Z","close_reason":"Superseded: restructuring complex arithmetic beads. The dependency on frankenjax-fij was wrong (pow already implemented), and the scope needs expansion.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"frankenjax-bw7","depends_on_id":"frankenjax-fij","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T23:27:32.452113994Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"frankenjax-bysv","title":"Add JAX oracle conformance for dynamic_update_slice clamping","description":"Add a committed fj-conformance integration test that freezes upstream JAX lax.dynamic_update_slice semantics for start-index normalization and clamping. The test should cover high positive starts clamped to the last valid update position, negative starts interpreted relative to the end, and multi-axis rank-2 starts. It should compare fj_lax::eval_primitive(Primitive::DynamicUpdateSlice) outputs against values captured from the JAX reference implementation, then validate with rch cargo test -p fj-conformance --test <new test> plus check/clippy/fmt for the touched scope.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:02:22.592273626Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:07:22.381378227Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T20:07:22.379575506Z","close_reason":"Added committed JAX oracle conformance test dynamic_update_slice_oracle.rs covering positive, negative, and per-axis clamped starts for lax.dynamic_update_slice; validated with rch test/check/clippy, fmt, and UBS.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
